item.title: Data Science
item.dc:creator: sharifur
item.content:encoded:
When data science as a professional field first came to the mainstream, traditional education wasnt ready to fully exploit its potential. The best way for someone to become a data scientist was learning through books, research papers, and online courses.

As Google trends shows, demand for learning data science is increasing over the last 12 months, and here at LearnWorlds, we see people interested in teaching and learning data science increasing over time. It is a trend that is here to stay!

item.title: Discover new world with gain knowledge.
item.dc:creator: ir_edus
item.content:encoded:
Very recently, I transitioned from a full-time agency job to doing the odd day for that agency as a freelancer and spending the rest of my time doing my own projects, websites, and ventures. If I didnt have a superstar or a boss, this would have been a difficult transition. With no set schedule (yet) its a challenge to know what to focus on next! Now to avoid this blog post turning into a giant wall of text and not many images (Im not actually sure if Ill put images in this at this point because its just not a focused post!) Ill include little headings as I usually do so that youre not going to get bored and click off this post!

Very recently, I transitioned from a full-time agency job to doing the odd day for that agency as a freelancer and spending the rest of my time doing my own projects, websites, and ventures. If I didnt have a superstar or a boss, this would have been a difficult transition.My boss was very understanding of the whole thing and we now have a great relationship and continue to be friends and work together. Good stuff! But switching from full-time work to full time working for yourself can be confusing

A cleansing hot shower or bath

Attention and mental energy is actually a resource and it DOES run out! Its easy to think that you can just focus on things all day long but you cant. Your brain is like a muscle, and because I cant really remember where I found this out, youre going to have to take my word for it, but there have been studies done proving this! Try and focus on things all day long 7 days a week, with no breaks. Youll find that at the very best, youre just not as effective towards the end of the days, and towards the end of the week

What relaxation looks like for you

  • Don't wear jeans under your white coat. It's unprofessional
  • Interns - don't spend all day long socializing over cups of coffee
  • Don't roll up the sleeves of your white coat. You're not a butcher
  • For the ladies - don't put on lots of makeup and perfume
  • Took time off to recuperate and recover my energy.

Very recently, I transitioned from a full-time agency job to doing the odd day for that agency as a freelancer and spending the rest of my time doing my own projects, websites, and ventures. If I didnt have a superstar or a boss, this would have been a difficult transition. With no set schedule (yet) its a challenge to know what to focus on next! Now to avoid this blog post turning into a giant wall of text and not many images (Im not actually sure if Ill put images in this at this point because its just not a focused post!) Ill include little headings as I usually do so that youre not going to get bored and click off this post!

Very recently, I transitioned from a full-time agency job to doing the odd day for that agency as a freelancer and spending the rest of my time doing my own projects, websites, and ventures. If I didnt have a superstar or a boss, this would have been a difficult transition.My boss was very understanding of the whole thing and we now have a great relationship and continue to be friends and work together. Good stuff! But switching from full-time work to full time working for yourself can be confusing

A cleansing hot shower or bath

Attention and mental energy is actually a resource and it DOES run out! Its easy to think that you can just focus on things all day long but you cant. Your brain is like a muscle, and because I cant really remember where I found this out, youre going to have to take my word for it, but there have been studies done proving this! Try and focus on things all day long 7 days a week, with no breaks. Youll find that at the very best, youre just not as effective towards the end of the days, and towards the end of the week

item.title: Undeniable Reasons to Love European Empires
item.dc:creator: nurfuad
item.content:encoded:
Very recently, I transitioned from a full-time agency job to doing the odd day for that agency as a freelancer and spending the rest of my time doing my own projects, websites, and ventures. If I didnt have a superstar or a boss, this would have been a difficult transition. With no set schedule (yet) its a challenge to know what to focus on next! Now to avoid this blog post turning into a giant wall of text and not many images (Im not actually sure if Ill put images in this at this point because its just not a focused post!) Ill include little headings as I usually do so that youre not going to get bored and click off this post!

Very recently, I transitioned from a full-time agency job to doing the odd day for that agency as a freelancer and spending the rest of my time doing my own projects, websites, and ventures. If I didnt have a superstar or a boss, this would have been a difficult transition.My boss was very understanding of the whole thing and we now have a great relationship and continue to be friends and work together. Good stuff! But switching from full-time work to full time working for yourself can be confusing

A cleansing hot shower or bath

Attention and mental energy is actually a resource and it DOES run out! Its easy to think that you can just focus on things all day long but you cant. Your brain is like a muscle, and because I cant really remember where I found this out, youre going to have to take my word for it, but there have been studies done proving this! Try and focus on things all day long 7 days a week, with no breaks. Youll find that at the very best, youre just not as effective towards the end of the days, and towards the end of the week

What relaxation looks like for you

  • Don't wear jeans under your white coat. It's unprofessional
  • Interns - don't spend all day long socializing over cups of coffee
  • Don't roll up the sleeves of your white coat. You're not a butcher
  • For the ladies - don't put on lots of makeup and perfume
  • Took time off to recuperate and recover my energy.

Viral dreamcatcher keytar typewriter, east hectic offal umami. Aesthetic polaroid pug pitchfork post-ironic.

item.title: Professional Skills and Career
item.dc:creator: nurfuad
item.content:encoded:
On another level, people are increasingly turning to online means to find a course that can help them improve their employability skills, successfully change a career, or advance in their chosen profession.
Currently, there seems to be an interest in professions related to Business, Marketing, Accounting, Computing, Data Science, Math and Real Estate that is likely to grow bigger.

item.title: Marketing
item.dc:creator: nurfuad
item.content:encoded:
Marketing courses are always relevant and can be tied well with any profession. But as the entrepreneurship route becomes more popular, the knowledge on how to set up your business, advertise and promote your services and products becomes vital.
Becoming familiar with digital marketing and social media, and learning how to invest in business branding, customer engagement, and measure marketing analytics is at the heart of all marketing initiatives.

item.title: Accounting
item.dc:creator: nurfuad
item.content:encoded:
Just like marketing, accounting is an integral part of business operations. As the years go by, a qualification in accounting will become essential for anyone to possess in order to be able to work in this field.
People who are good with numbers and mostly dealing with money are getting more interested in becoming accountants and this is evident through the number of google searches on online accounting courses
